For Validating XML Files
Install XML Utilities


sudo apt-get install libxml2-utils
Validate XML File
Replace test.xml with the name of your XML file:

bash
Copy code
xmllint --noout test.xml
Command Explanation:
xmllint: A tool for parsing and validating XML.
--noout: Suppresses output if the file is valid. Errors will still be displayed.














For Validating JSON Files
Install JSON Processor (jq)


sudo apt-get install jq
Validate JSON File
Replace test.json with the name of your JSON file:


jq . test.json
